ld animal: 15 + TL\\nMonster of animal intelligence: +5',NULL,NULL),(48,'Train Animal',1,NULL,'d20 + Animal Empathy skill + Cha mod vs. DC','Var (25% time)','C, V, S','Var (feed)','Close','Instantaneous','One trainable animal','You train an animal for a specific purpose or teach it a new trick.','S – The training succeeds. You can now use Handle Animal to get the animal to perform accordingly.\\nF – The training fails, but you may try again.','Train for combat riding (6 w): 20 (attack, come, defend, down, guard, heel)\\nTrain for fighting (3 w): 20 (attack, down, stay)\\nTrain for guarding (4 w): 20 (attack, defend, down, guard)\\nTrain for heavy labor (2 w): 15 (come, work)\\nTrain for homing (5 w): 20 (come, fetch, heel, return home)\\nTrain for hunting (6 w): 20 (attack, down, fetch, heel, seek, track)\\nTrain for performance (5 w): 15 (come, fetch, heel, perform, stay)\\nTrain for riding (3 w): 15 (come, heel, stay)\\nTeach a simple trick (1 w): 15 (come, down, fetch, heel, perform, seek, stay, or work)\\nTeach an advanced trick (1 w): 20 (attack, defend, guard, track, return home)\\nTeach unusual movement (1 w): 25 (aerial or aquatic movement through magic)\\nMonster of animal intelligence: +5','Animal companion: +4 circ',NULL),(49,'Jump',2,'[Untrained, Move, T10]','d20 + Athletics skill + Str mod + PAM + EP','1 MP per sq',NULL,'1 SP','Personal',NULL,'You','You attempt to jump a certain vertical or horizontal distance. Unless you want to land prone, you have to accept a penalty (see below).\\nIf you have a suitable pole (note that a quarterstaff or spear qualifies) and a place to plant it, you can turn a running jump into a pole vaulting jump. Pole vaulting is more difficult, but it lets you add the pole’s length to either the vertical or horizontal distance cleared.','With a standing long jump, you can cover a horizontal distance of check × 0.15 m. You clear a vertical height ¼ of the horizontal distance.\\nWith a standing high jump, you can clear a vertical height of check × 0.05 m.\\nWith a running long jump, you can cover a horizontal distance of check × 0.3 m. You clear a vertical height ¼ of the horizontal distance.\\nWith a running high jump, you can clear a vertical height of check × 0.1 m.\\nIf your check is 0 or less, you stumble and fall prone at the start of the jump.',NULL,'Speed modifier: -6 + (base speed in squares)\\nLand on feet: -5\\nPole vaulting: -5\\nAcrobatics synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(50,'Climb',2,'[Untrained, Move, AoO]','d20 + Athletics skill + Str mod + PAM + EP vs. DC','Depends on race','Hands and feet','1 SP per r','Personal','1 r','You','If your race has the climbing trait, this action can be used to scale a cliff, a wall, or a steep slope.\\nYou need both hands and feet to climb, but you can cling to a wall with one hand and use the other to make attacks or cast somatic spells.\\nWhile climbing, you can only use passive DeC (unless your race has a climb speed).','S – You can use your MP to climb up, down, or across.\\nF – No climbing progress. You can try again next round.\\nOF – You fall.','Less than 60° incline, or knotted rope and wall: 0\\nRope and wall, or knotted rope: 5\\nRigging, or surface with edges: 10\\nSurface with handholds, or unknotted rope: 15\\nUneven surface, typical dungeon wall: 20\\nNatural cliff, or brick wall: 25\\nOverhang, or ceiling with handholds: 25\\nSmooth, flat, vertical surface: 40\\nIf you can create your own handholds (with pitons or an axe), the DC becomes 15.\\nBracing against opposite wall: -10\\nBracing against corner wall: -5\\nSlippery: +5\\nCatch yourself when falling: +15\\nCatch someone else falling: +10','Fast climb (halve MP per sq): -5\\nRacial climb speed: +8 racial\\nClimber’s kit: +2 circ\\nAcrobatics synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls\\nSurvival synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls',1),(51,'Swim or Dive',2,'[Untrained, Move, T10]','d20 + Athletics skill + Str mod + PAM + 2 × EP vs. DC','4 MP per sq','Arms and legs','1 SP per min','Personal','1 r','You','