by your skill level. Except as noted above, this is a grade III shapechange.\\nSkill level 16: You can turn into small, medium, or large elementals.\\nSkill level 20: You can also turn into huge elementals.\\nSkill level 24: You can also turn into any elemental creature up to huge size.','S – You alter your shape successfully.\\nF – You fail to alter shape but can try again.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(189,'Wild Shape',11,'[Su]','(d20 + Wild Shape skill + Wis mod + PAM)','9 AP','C','10 SP','Personal','1 day (D)','You','You alter your shape into an animal or plant, according to the limitations given by your skill level.\\nIf you are wounded, you regain TL HP when returning to your natural form.\\nExcept as noted above, this is a grade II shapechange.\\nSkill level 3: You gain the ability to turn into any normal (and immobile) plant of small or medium size. While in plant form, you have your regular senses and abilities of observation, but you have Dex 0, base speed 0, and no ability to speak or cast spells with verbal, somatic, or material components.\\nSkill level 5: You gain the ability to turn into any animal of small or medium size. Most forms will only allow casting of spells without verbal, somatic, and material components.\\nSkill level 8: You can also turn into large animals and plants.\\nSkill level 11: You can also turn into tiny animals and plants.\\nSkill level 12: You can also turn into plant creatures.\\nSkill level 15: You can also turn into huge animals and plants.','S – You alter your shape successfully.\\nF – You fail to alter shape but can try again.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(190,'Control Transformation',11,'[Su, Untrained]','d20 + Lycanthropic Control skill + Wis mod + PAM vs. DC','Reaction or full-round','C',NULL,'Personal','Instantaneous','You','You either try to resist an involuntary transformation or to trigger a voluntary one.\\nAs a lycanthrope, you may involuntarily change into your animal form. This happens during the nights of a full moon and every time you first take damage during a combat encounter. You are allowed a Control Transformation check to avoid changing shape. The shapechange is a grade II change.\\nSkill level 1: You are now able to attempt voluntary changes to your animal form and back to humanoid form.\\nSkill level 2: You are now able to attempt voluntary changes to and from a hybrid form. This too is a grade II shapechange. You still need to make checks to remember your actions and to avoid alignment change.\\nSkill level 5: You no longer need to make checks to remember your actions or avoid alignment change.\\nSkill level 8: The change of shape now takes 6 AP instead of a full round.','S – You manage to resist or trigger the transformation.\\nF – You fail to resist or trigger the change. If it is an involuntary change or a change to humanoid form, it takes 1 day before you can retry.','Resist involuntary change: 25\\nVoluntary change to humanoid form (full moon): 25\\nVoluntary change to humanoid form (not full moon): 20\\nVoluntary change to hybrid form: 15\\nVoluntary change to animal form (full moon): 15\\nVoluntary change to animal form (not full moon): 20',NULL,NULL),(191,'Gaze Attack',11,'[Su]','d20 + Body & Mind skill mod + PAM + AB vs. Fort','6 AP','C, vision',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(192,'Elan Psi Defense',11,'[Su]',NULL,'3 AP','C','2 PP','Personal','1 r','You','Gain +4 racial bonus to Fort, Ref, or Will for 1 round.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(193,'Elan Psi Conversion',11,'[Su]',NULL,'Reaction',NULL,'Spcl','Personal','Instantaneous','You','Once per round, when taking HP or SP damage, you can choose to convert all or part of it to PP damage.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(194,'Xeph Psi Burst',2,'[Su]',NULL,'0 AP','C','3 PP','Personal','1 r','You','Gain +1 racial bonus to speed for 1 round.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(197,'Psi Cannibalization',11,'[Su]',NULL,'4 AP','C','Spcl','Personal','Instantaneous','You','You can recover PP at the expense of your own health. You recover 2 PP per point of ability damage to each of your physical ability scores (Str, Con, and Dex). For example, you can sacrifice 2 points of Str and 1 point of Dex to regain 6 PP.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(198,'Speed of Thought',2,'[Su]',NULL,'0 AP',NULL,'3 PP','Personal','1 r','You','Speed of Thought: You can spend 3 PP to gain a +1 enhancement bonus to speed for 1 round.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(199,'Mental Leap',2,'[Su, Move]',NULL,'Part of jump',NULL,'3 PP','Personal','Part of jump','You','Mental Leap: Whenever you make an Athletics/Jump check, you can spend 3 PP to gain a +10 enhancement bonus.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(200,'Psionic Dodge',9,'[Su]',NULL,'0 AP',NULL,'3 PP','Personal','1 r','You','Psionic Dodge: You can spend 3 PP to gain a +2 dodge bonus to DeC for 1 round.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(201,'Psionic Flanking',6,'[Su]',NULL,'0 AP',NULL,'3 PP','Personal','1 r','Spcl','Psionic Flanking: You can spend 3 PP to gain a +4 flanking bonus against an opponent for 1 round.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(202,'Up the Walls',2,'[Su, Move]',NULL,'Part of move',NULL,'1 PP',NULL,'1 sq','You','Up the Walls: By spending 1 PP as part of movement, you can move 1 square along a wall or similar vertical surface. By spending additional PP, you can keep traversing the wall, until you reach a horizontal surface (or fall down).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(203,'Ghost Attack',6,'[Su]',NULL,'As per weapon','As per weapon','+3 PP','As per weapon','One attack','As per weapon','Ghost Attack: When you are about to make a weapon attack (with a natural, melee, or ranged weapon), you can choose to spend 3 PP to infuse it with psionic energy. The attack will then cause normal damage against incorporeal targets.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(204,'Penetrating Attack',6,'[Su]',NULL,'As per weapon','As per weapon','+3 PP','As per weapon','One attack','As per weapon','Penetrating Attack: When you are about to make a weapon attack (with a natural, melee, or ranged weapon), you can choose to spend 3 PP to infuse it with psionic energy. For this attack, halve the target’s DR.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(205,'Aligned Attack',6,'[Su]',NULL,'As per weapon','As per weapon','+3 PP','As per weapon','One attack','As per weapon','Aligned Attack: When you are about to make a weapon attack (with a natural, melee, or ranged weapon), you can choose to spend 3 PP to infuse it with psionic energy of a specific alignment (must match your own alignment, at least partially). The attack counts as an aligned attack of the appropriate type, with respect to aligned DR. Furthermore, with a successful hit, you deal an additional 1d6 HP of damage.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(206,'Power Attack',6,'[Su]',NULL,'As per weapon','As per weapon','+3/6 PP','As per weapon','One attack','As per weapon','Power Attack: When you are about to make a weapon attack (with a natural, melee, or ranged weapon), you can choose to spend 3 PP to infuse it with psionic energy. With a successful hit, you deal an additional 2d6 HP of damage.\\nLvl 15 - Greater Power Attack: Same as Power Attack, but you can spend 6 PP to increase the damage by 4d6 HP.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(207,'Wounding Attack',6,'[Su]',NULL,'As per weapon','As per weapon','+3 PP','As per weapon','One attack','As per weapon','Wounding Attack: When you are about to make a weapon attack (with a natural, melee, or ranged weapon), you can choose to spend 3 PP to infuse it with psionic energy. With a successful hit, you deal 1 point of Con damage (in addition to the normal weapon damage).',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(208,'Use Influence',10,'[Lang]','d20 + influence + Cha mod + other mods vs. DC or opposing Psychology (Sense Motive)','1+ min','V',NULL,'Close','Instantaneous','Invidividual or organization','You exert your power over the target and request their help with something.','S - The target provides you with minimal aid.\\nCS - The target provides you with as much aid as they possibly can.\\nF - The target regretfully denies your request.\\nCF - The target becomes a new enemy.','Request shelter (small party): 12\\nGain access to news and gossip: 12\\nRequest lodging (large party or extended stay): 15\\nFresh supplies and horses (small party): 18\\nMedicines and treatment for wounded: 18\\nConfirm rights, legitimacy, or resolve minor dispute: 18\\nLend use of expert: 20\\nConfirm rights, legitimacy, or resolve significant dispute: 20\\nRequest protection from lesser authority: 25\\nConfirm rights, legitimacy, or resolve major dispute: 25\\nLend use of small company or several experts: 30\\nRequest protection from equal authority: 35\\nLend use of major military force: 35\\nRequest protection from greater authority: 40','Using group influence against individual target: -10\\nDifference in SC (social class): ±4 per rank\\nTarget has family ties or sworn direct service to you: +5\\nTarget has friendly attitude: +5\\nTarget has hostile attitude: -5\\nPerform service for target: Varies\\nBribe, gift, or blackmail: Varies\\nDanger or inconvenience for target: Varies\\nApplicable reputation: +½ or -½ reputation value\\nHelpful influence from third party: +(Up to the third party’s influence)\\nOpposing influence from third party: -(Up to the third party’s influence)\\nClearing debt (works only on individuals): By permanently reducing your influence, you gain a corresponding bonus.',1),(209,'Earn Money',10,'[Untrained]','d20 + Knowledge skill + Int mod','1 week (50% time)','C, (tools)','Special','Personal',NULL,'You','You use your skill to advice, teach, or perform research.','If you are in a location where you can get a job and perform your skill, you earn half the check result in silver pieces.',NULL,'Untrained use: -5 circ\\nImprovised tools: -2 circ\\nMasterwork tools: +2 circ',NULL),(210,'Earn Money',10,'[Untrained]','d20 + Profession skill + Wis mod','1 week (50% time)','C, (tools)','Special','Personal',NULL,'You','You use your skill to gain employment and make money.','If you are in a location where you can get a job and perform your skill, you earn half the check result in silver pieces.',NULL,'Untrained use: -5 circ\\nImprovised tools: -2 circ\\nMasterwork tools: +2 circ',NULL),(211,'Perform',10,'[Untrained, T10]','d20 + Perform skill + Cha mod vs. DC','1 day (50% time)','C',NULL,'LoS',NULL,'Audience','You use your skill to entertain an audience.','S – You impress the audience enough to make money.\\nF – You do not impress the audience and make no money.','Routine performance: 10 (earns 1d6 cp/day)\\nEnjoyable performance: 15 (earns 1d6 sp/day)\\nGreat performance: 20 (earns 3d6 sp/day)\\nMemorable performance: 25 (earns 1d6 gp/day)\\nExtraordinary performance: 30 (earns 3d6 gp/day)\\nUnimpressed audience: +2 per previous failure','Acrobatics synergy: +1 syn per 5 lvls for dancing specialization\\nMasterwork instrument: +2 circ for instrument specialties',NULL),(212,'Know Answer',1,'[Untrained, Secret]','d20 + Enemy Specialization skill + Int mod vs. DC','0 AP',NULL,NULL,'Personal','Instantaneous','You','You try to recall details about one of your specialized creatures.','S – You remember the answer.\\nF – You don’t know the correct answer and cannot retry until your skill improves.\\nCF – You recall the wrong answer.','Identify a monster: 10 + CL (levels of success → powers and vulnerabilities)',NULL,1),(213,'Inflict Disease',11,'[Su, AoO]','Touch attack vs. DeC','9 AP','C, S','10 PP','Tch','Instantaneous','1 living creature','You try to inflict the target with a disease (see Affliction spell).','S – The target contracts the chosen disease.\\nF – You miss the target.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(214,'Reload Projectile Weapon',4,'[Untrained, AoO]',NULL,'Var','C, projectile weapon',NULL,'Personal',NULL,'You','You reload an equipped projectile weapon. See the weapon list for AP cost.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(215,'Speak',1,'[Untrained, Lang]',NULL,'0 AP','V',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You can say anything that can normally be said in a few seconds.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(216,'Lower Magic Resistance',11,'[Untrained]',NULL,'5 AP',NULL,NULL,'Personal','1 r','You','You lower your MR to any level you desire, between 0 and your full MR.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(217,'Drink Potion',8,'[Untrained, AoO]',NULL,'5 AP','Hand, potion',NULL,'Personal',NULL,'You','You drink a potion, and it takes effect immediately. Note that this action does not include retrieving the potion.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(218,'Administer Potion',8,'[Untrained, AoO]',NULL,'10 AP','Hand, potion',NULL,'Tch',NULL,'1 creature','You pour a potion into another creature, and it takes effect immediately. Retrieving the potion is not included in this action, so that takes additional time.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(219,'Apply Oil to Skin or Surface',8,'[Untrained, AoO]',NULL,'5 AP','Hand, oil',NULL,'Tch',NULL,'You or 1 creature','You pour oil onto your own skin or that of someone else. Some oils can also be applied to an object.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(220,'Read Scroll',7,'[Su, AoO]','Spellcasting check vs. PL + DC','Spell’s ×2','Vision, V',NULL,'Per spell','Per spell','Per spell','You read a spell scroll to activate the written spell. You have to use the spellcasting skills (and ability modifiers) that you would use to cast the original spell.','S - You successfully read the scroll, and its spell activates.\\nF - The spell fizzles. The scroll is consumed.\\nCF - You miscast the spell and suffer a mishap.',NULL,'Same as for spellcasting.',1),(221,'Mental Item Activation',8,'[Untrained]',NULL,'6 AP',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You activate a magic item with a mental command.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(222,'Command Item Activation',8,'[Untrained]',NULL,'6 AP','V',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL,'You activate a magic item with a verbal command.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(223,'Vital Stun Attack',6,NULL,'(Vital attack) plus (d20 + Vital Attack skill / 2 + Int mod + MAM + AB vs. Fort)','Part of vital attack','C, as per weapon','1 SP','As per attack','Var','As per attack','By exchanging 2d6 of vital attack damage, you can make a special attack to stun the victim.','S – The victim is stunned for 1 round.\\nES - The victim is stunned for 1d6 rounds.\\nF – The stun attack fails but still deals the reduced vital attack damage.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(224,'Open or Close Door',8,'[Untrained]',NULL,'4 AP','Hand',NULL,'Tch','Instantaneous','1 door','You either open or close a door of typical size (if it is not stuck or locked).',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(225,'Redirect Spell',7,'[Su]',NULL,'6 AP',NULL,NULL,'As per spell','Instantaneous','Active spell','Some active spells can be redirected at new targets (if you are still within the original range).',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(226,'Dismiss Spell',7,'[Su]',NULL,'4 AP',NULL,NULL,'As per spell','Instantaneous','Dismissable spell','Some active spells can be dismissed with this action before their normal duration has expired.',NULL,NULL,NULL,1),(227,'Poison Breath',6,'[Poison]','d20 + Area Attack skill mod + Dex mod + PAM + AB vs. Fort','6 AP (once/r)','C, breath','10 SP','0','Instantaneous','3 sq cone','You expel a cone of poison through your mouth.','S – The affected creature suffers full effect.\\nF – The creature suffers no or reduced effect.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(228,'Energy Breath',11,'[Su]','d20 + Area Attack skill mod + Dex mod + PAM + AB vs. Ref','6 AP (once/r)','C, breath','10 SP','0','Instantaneous','6 sq cone','You expel a cone of the appropriate energy type through your mouth.','S – The affected creature suffers full damage.\\nCS – The target takes double damage.\\nF – The creature suffers only half damage.\\nCF – The target takes no damage.',NULL,NULL,NULL),(229,'Change Shape',11,'[Su]',NULL,'9 AP','C','10 SP','Personal','Var','You','You alter your shape, according to the limitations given by your ability.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(230,'Ink Cloud',9,NULL,NULL,'2 AP (once/r)','C','10 SP','0','Encounter','2 sq radius','You expel an ink cloud that provides total concealment.',NULL,NULL,NULL,NULL),(231,'Teleport',11,'[Su, Teleport]',NULL,'6 AP','C','5 PP','Personal','Instantaneous','You','You instantly transport yourself (and your carried belongings)