 evil deities, but a few neutral ones have also been known to teach it to their templars.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Paladin class.'),(169,'Divine Smiting','DvSmi',8,NULL,NULL,'Divine Smiting is a skill that helps you identify and punish the enemies of your deity. This skill is primarily taught by churches of good or evil deities, but a few neutral ones have also been known to teach it to their templars.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Paladin class.'),(170,'Enchant Item','EncIt',8,1,NULL,'Enchant Item is a combination of all the skills used for creating magic devices, animating constructs, imbuing objects with intelligence, transferring power from one item to another, etc. A magic item that has been partially damaged loses none of its magic and can still be repaired with the appropriate Crafting specialization.'),(171,'Familiar','Famil',8,NULL,NULL,'Familiar is a skill that lets you summon a special animal to serve as your familiar. As your skill level increases, you can either improve your familiar (see Rules of Culture for details) or replace it with a more versatile creature. Unless the DM specifically allows it, you can never have more than one familiar. If a familiar dies or is dismissed/replaced by you, it will take one year before a new one can be summoned. The familiar must be an animal or monstrous animal at least one size category smaller than you, and the CL of your familiar must not exceed your skill level. If the DM allows multiple familiars, the sum of their CL must not exceed your skill level.\\nEmpathic Link [Su]: You can communicate empathically with your familiar to a range of 1 km (no AP cost).\\nWhen the familiar is within 1 sq, you gain a +2 skill level bonus on Perception.\\nWhen the familiar is within 1 km, you gain a +2 skill level bonus on one of the familiar’s racial skills (chosen when the familiar is summoned).\\nAny spell you cast on yourself can automatically affect your familiar as well (1 sq range; no extra cost).\\nWhen the familiar is within 1 sq, it can use your Fort, Ref, and Will defenses (if they are better).\\nInspired by the 3.5E Sorcerer and Wizard classes.'),(172,'Ki - Defense','KiDef',8,NULL,NULL,'Ki - Defense is an almost supernatural ability to focus your inner strength and use it to defend against attacks.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Monk class.'),(173,'Ki - Meditation','KiMed',8,NULL,NULL,'Ki - Meditation is the ability to focus your inner strength and gain a number of almost supernatural abilities.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Monk class.'),(174,'Ki - Mobility','KiMob',8,NULL,NULL,'Ki - Mobility is the ability to focus your inner strength and use it to enhance your speed and mobility.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Monk class.'),(175,'Ki - Offense','KiOff',8,NULL,NULL,'Ki - Offense is the ability to focus your inner strength and use it to enhance your natural weapon attacks.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Monk class.'),(176,'Metamorphosis - Celestial','MmCel',8,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcCo)>=5 OR Skl(DivSu)>=5)','Metamorphosis - Celestial is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into a celestial creature. This transformation can involve arcane rituals, bargains with celestial beings, awakening a dormant bloodline, et al.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Celestial bloodline and celestial template.'),(177,'Metamorphosis - Demonic','MmDem',8,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcCo)>=5 OR Skl(DivSu)>=5)','Metamorphosis - Demonic is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into a demonic creature. This transformation can involve arcane rituals, bargains with demons, awakening a dormant bloodline, et al.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Demonic bloodline and fiendish template.'),(178,'Metamorphosis - Diabolic','MmDia',8,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcCo)>=5 OR Skl(DivSu)>=5)','Metamorphosis - Diabolic is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into a diabolic creature. This transformation can involve arcane rituals, bargains with devils, awakening a dormant bloodline, et al.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Diabolic bloodline and fiendish template.'),(179,'Metamorphosis - Draconic','MmDra',8,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND Skl(ArcTr)>=5','Metamorphosis - Draconic is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into a draconic creature.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Dragon Disciple prestige class, Draconic bloodline, and half-dragon template.'),(180,'Metamorphosis - Air Elemental','MmAEl',8,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcEn)>=5 OR Skl(DivLi)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcTr)>=5 OR Skl(DivNa)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcAe)>=5 OR Skl(DivEl)>=5)','Metamorphosis - Air Elemental is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into an elemental creature.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Elemental bloodlines and genasi race.'),(181,'Metamorphosis - Earth Elemental','MmEEl',8,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcEn)>=5 OR Skl(DivLi)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcTr)>=5 OR Skl(DivNa)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcLi)>=5 OR Skl(DivEl)>=5)','Metamorphosis - Earth Elemental is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into an elemental creature.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Elemental bloodlines and genasi race.'),(182,'Metamorphosis - Fire Elemental','MmFEl',8,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcEn)>=5 OR Skl(DivLi)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcTr)>=5 OR Skl(DivNa)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcPy)>=5 OR Skl(DivEl)>=5)','Metamorphosis - Fire Elemental is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into an elemental creature.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Elemental bloodlines and genasi race.'),(183,'Metamorphosis - Water Elemental','MmWEl',8,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND (Skl(ArcEn)>=5 OR Skl(DivLi)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcTr)>=5 OR Skl(DivNa)>=5) AND (Skl(ArcHy)>=5 OR Skl(DivEl)>=5)','Metamorphosis - Water Elemental is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into an elemental creature.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Elemental bloodlines and genasi race.'),(184,'Metamorphosis - Fey','MmFey',8,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND Skl(DivEl)>=5','Metamorphosis - Fey is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into a fey creature.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Fey bloodline.'),(185,'Metamorphosis - Golem','MmGol',8,NULL,'Skl(Craft)>=5 AND Skl(ArcEn)>=5 AND Skl(EncIt)>=5','Metamorphosis - Golem is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into a mechanically enhanced creature.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Half-Golem template.'),(186,'Metamorphosis - Incorporeal','MmInc',8,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND Skl(PsiPk)>=5 AND Skl(PsiPp)>=5','Metamorphosis - Incorporeal is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into an incorporeal creature.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Psion Uncarnate prestige class.'),(187,'Metamorphosis - Shadow','MmSha',8,NULL,'Skl(SplCr)>=5 AND Skl(ArcTr)>=5 AND Skl(SWAff)>=5','Metamorphosis - Shadow is not so much a true skill as it is a gradual transformation into a creature infused with shadowstuff (often referred to as a shade).\\nInspired by the 3.5E shade template.'),(188,'Pseudomagic','PsMag',8,NULL,NULL,'Pseudomagic is a skill that can be used to activate magic devices that would normally require skills, special abilities, or an alignment that you do not possess.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Rogue class.'),(189,'Psicrystal','PsCry',8,NULL,NULL,'Psicrystal is a skill that lets you infuse a crystal with a part of your own personality. As your skill level increases, your psicrystal improves in powers and versatility. You can never have more than one psicrystal. If a psicrystal is destroyed, it will take one year before a new one can be created.\\nTelepathic Link [Su]: You can communicate telepathically with your psicrystal to a range of 1 km (no AP cost).\\nWhen the psicrystal is within 1 sq, you gain a +2 skill level bonus on Perception.\\nWhen the psicrystal is within 1 km, you gain a bonus based on the crystal’s personality.\\nAny power you manifest on yourself can automatically affect your psicrystal as well (1 sq range; no extra cost).\\nWhen the psicrystal is within 1 sq, it can use your Fort, Ref, and Will defenses (if they are better than its own).\\nInspired by the 3.5E Psion class.'),(190,'Psionic Mobility','PsMob',8,NULL,NULL,'Psionic Mobility is an ability that lets you use mental strength to enhance your speed and mobility.\\nInspired by the 3.5E psionic feats.'),(191,'Psionic Offense','PsOff',8,NULL,NULL,'Psionic Offense is an ability that lets you use mental strength to enhance your weapon attacks.\\nInspired by the 3.5E psionic feats.'),(192,'Pyrokinetics','Pyrok',8,NULL,'Skl(ArcPy)>=5 OR Skl(PsiPk)>=5','Pyrokinetics is a supernatural ability that lets you create and control fire in different forms. Most individuals who learn this skill have volatile, chaotic, and violent personalities, and they are not welcome in most civilized societies.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Pyrokineticist prestige class.'),(193,'Shadowdancing','ShaDa',8,NULL,'Skl(Steal)>=7 AND Skl(Acrob)>=7 AND Skl(CmbIn)>=7','Shadowdancing is a skill that gradually strengthens your connection to the Plane of Shadow and gives you supernatural abilities related to that plane.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Shadowdancer prestige class.'),(194,'Soulknife','SouKn',8,NULL,'Skl(WpLtB)>=3 AND Skl(PsiPm)>=3','Soulknife is a supernatural ability that lets you use psionic energy to manifest a semi-real blade of force.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Soulknife class.'),(195,'Spellcraft','SplCr',8,NULL,NULL,'Spellcraft is a skill that develops your sensitivity to and proficiency with supernatural energies.'),(196,'Spellfire','SplFi',8,NULL,'Skl(ArcAb)>=13 AND Skl(ArcKi)>=13 AND Skl(ArcPy)>=13 AND Skl(ArcTr)>=13','Spellfire is the rare and powerful ability to summon and shape raw arcane energy. Powerful sorcerers and wizards sometimes learn this skill, but the most skilled spellfire wielders are the precious few born with the ability. Spellfire is a more instinctive use of magic than ordinary spellcasting. While most magic is mentally taxing, a spellfire wielder instead uses his physical stamina.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Spellfire feat.'),(197,'Wild Shape','WldSh',8,NULL,NULL,'Wild Shape is a supernatural skill that lets you assume the shapes of various animals and eventually plants and elementals.\\nInspired by the 3.5E Druid class.'),(198,'Ghost Manifestation','Ghost',9,NULL,'Race==Ghost','Ghost Manifestation is a skill that ghosts (and maybe other incorporeal undead creatures) use to improve their influence over the physical world.'),(199,'Lycanthropic Control','Lycan',9,NULL,'CrSubt==Lycanthrope','Lycanthropic Control is a skill that lycanthropic creatures use to improve and control their supernatural abilities. Natural (inherited) lycanthropes usually learn this skill as part of their upbringing, while those with acquired lycanthropy gain access to it when they contract the disease.'),(200,'Vampire Powers','VampP',9,NULL,'Race==Vampire','Vampire Powers is a skill that vampires learn to gradually improve their supernatural abilities and gain new ones.'),(201,'Fighting Style - Power Attack','FSPow',3,NULL,NULL,'Fighting Style - Power Attack is a skill that focuses on strong melee attacks, favoring heavy and usually two-handed weapons.'),(202,'Fighting Style - Precision','FSPre',3,NULL,NULL,'Fighting Style - Precision is a skill that focuses on precision attacks, improving your chance of striking even the most elusive and agile opponents.'),(203,'Fighting Style - Trickery','FSTri',3,NULL,NULL,'Fighting Style - Trickery is a skill that focuses on special combat maneuvers, typically ones used to disarm, trip, or confuse your opponents.'),(204,'Lich Powers','LichP',9,NULL,'Race==Lich','Lich Powers is a skill that liches learn to gradually improve their supernatural abilities and gain new ones.'),(205,'Dragon Affinity','DracA',9,NULL,'CrType==Dragon','Dragon Affinity represents the natural affinity a dragon has for spellcasting.');
