es the specified fraction of a round to complete or initiate the action. Deduct the same fraction of the creature’s action points and movement points (rounded up) for this round.',NULL),(10,'AP','AP        ',0,'The specified number of action points must be spent to complete or initiate the action. If you have an insufficient number of AP left of your turn, you can spend your remaining AP to initiate the action and pay the rest on your next turn. For many actions, interruption is then possible and may require skill checks to maintain concentration until the action is finished.',NULL),(11,'MP','MP',0,'The specified number of movement points must be spent to complete or initiate the action. If you have an insufficient number of MP left of your turn, you cannot initiate the action.',NULL),(12,'Encounter','enc       ',100,NULL,'The effect ends when the current encounter ends. If this is used outside of an encounter, the duration is limited to approximately 1 minute per skill level.'),(13,'Instantaneous','instant   ',0,NULL,'The actual effect lasts only an instant, but its consequences may be long-lasting or permanent.'),(14,'Permanent','perm      ',100000000,NULL,'The effect has unlimited duration. If it is magical in nature, however, it can still be dispelled.'),(15,'Concentration','conc      ',0,NULL,'The effect lasts for as long as concentration is maintained (and sometimes an additional specified duration after that). While concentrating, you can spend only half your AP and MP each round on other actions (and only on actions without the concentration implement). An action that triggers attacks of opportunity (AoO) will trigger another AoO at the beginning of each round of concentration. Every situation that can break your concentration will typically require a new skill check. An action that costs SP to initiate requires 1 SP per round of concentration, and an action that costs PP to initiate requires 1 PP per round of concentration.'),(16,'Reaction','react',0,'This 